In order to understand the structures and characteristics of the as-grown crystals, the crystallinity was confirmed in the X-ray powder diffraction (XRD) patterns as shown in Fig. 1(b). It can be seen from the XRD spectra of Er3+/Yb3+ co-doped Na5Lu9F32 single crystal in Fig. 1(b), the structure of the single crystal was confirmed to be cubic phase, in accordance with JCPDS card (27–0725) of Na5Lu9F32 as shown in Fig. 1(c), which the diffraction peak positions of the obtained samples doped with Er3+/Yb3+ ions are matched perfectly with those of standard Na5Lu9F32, though there exists a slight shift in the range of 0.10° to 0.45° as the dopant change, indicating that this transparent crystal has pure cubic phase. Moreover, the cell parameters were calculated by the following formula181d=ah2+k2+l2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
